All those talks about the food and the shelter becomes meaningless when we cannot have transportation allowances for them to buy food and clothes for them. Most, if not all of these organizations working for refugees' causes had repeatedly been asked about their willingness than to bear part of the monthly expenses only to get evasive answers.

"We will pay for shelter and food only" said one guy working in Iraq for SVN (Single Volunteer Network). "Who pays medical bills and the transportation costs?" I asked. The guy was totally blank. I summed up and asked him if he will provide the refugees with jobs and that means food and shelter. My feeling coz I was non-paying and no guarantee commission worked and he got in his pocket around 12,000USD and I got only 5,000USD.

The recent edict by the Senate, in fact, hurts the refugees' cause. It's simple equation to follow. 20,000 refugees means 20,000 families and all of them have their own basic needs. Migration is not the solution, nor is political representation according to the proposed report by the Senate. When the Senate brings three alternatives: migration, cultural autonomy, or political representation, they miss political asylum as an option.
